{
  "texts": [
    "Fine-tuning addresses this limitation by updating the parameters of a pre-trained model using task-specific data, thereby adapting the model's knowledge and capabilities to better address the nuances of a particular task.",
    "The fine-tuning process typically involves several key steps.",
    "First, a pre-trained LLM that better aligns with the task requirements is selected.",
    "Next, it is acquired a dataset relevant to the target task, which may include labeled examples or annotated text data, that will serve as the training data for fine-tuning the LLM.",
    "During fine-tuning, the pre-trained LLM's parameters are adjusted accordingly to the task-specific dataset through a process known as backpropagation [34]."
  ]
}